:: Begin Game → Scenario 1 - Vision Impairment {"position":"1500,300","size":"100,100"}
- Scenario 1 - Vision Impairment
You are designing a website for a university. The design team suggests using **red and green indicators** for errors and success messages.

What do you do?


Option 1.
[[Use red and green text for errors and success messages.]]  
<img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/5787796/pexels-photo-5787796.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" 
alt="Example of red and green text for errors and success messages, which is inaccessible for people with color blindness." width="600">

Option 2.
[[Use black text on a white background, add symbols/icons for messages.]]  
<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507238691740-187a5b1d37b8?w=700&auto=format&fit=crop&q=60&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxzZWFyY2h8Mnx8YWNjZXNzaWJsZSUyMHdlYnNpdGV8ZW58MHx8MHx8fDA%3D" 
alt="Example of an accessible website with black text on a white background and symbols/icons to improve readability." width="600">



:: Don't do anything, let them struggle. {"position":"1600,1400","size":"100,100"}
- Don't do anything, let them struggle.
❌ **Incorrect!**

Leaving them without assistance creates an **unnecessary barrier**. Accessibility should be **available to all**.

→ [[Next Scenario → Scenario 7 - Muscular Dystrophy]]



:: Encourage the cashier to be patient and allow the customer time to communicate. {"position":"1600,1000","size":"100,100"}
- Encourage the cashier to be patient and allow the customer time to communicate.
✅ **Correct!**

People with **speech impairments** may need **extra time** to communicate. **Patience ensures dignity and respect**.

(set: $score to $score + 1)

→ [[Next Scenario → Scenario 5 - Prosthetic Limb Use]]



:: Ensure there’s a ramp and elevator access. {"position":"1600,800","size":"100,100"}
- Ensure there’s a ramp and elevator access.
✅ **Correct!**

Ramps and **elevators allow wheelchair users** and others with **mobility impairments** to access the space.

(set: $score to $score + 1)

→ [[Next Scenario → Scenario 4 - Speech Impairment]]



